15/09/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A delegation representing the city of Mostar in Bosnia and Herzegovina visited Zagreb on Friday (12 September) to discuss measures for boosting economic relations. 
Mostar Mayor Hamdija Jahic said the municipalities would consider opening a direct air link with Croatia Airlines, as well as construction projects.
In other news, Air Bosnia was forced to suspend operations on Friday after banks froze its accounts because of unpaid debts totaling nearly 7m euros. 
Company officials said they did not know when flights would resume. 
(Dnevni Avaz - 15/09/03; Onasa, BBC - 14/09/03; AFP - 12/09/03)
